$

To make sure that the loot is divided evenly, the first thief should pick up at least one coin of the highest denomination ($2^{k-1}$), and the second thief should pick up at least one coin of the second highest denomination ($2^{k-2}$). This means that the first thief can pick up $x_{k-1} \cdot x_{k-2} \cdots x_0$ coins of the highest denomination, and the second thief can pick up $x_{k-1} \cdot x_{k-2} \cdots x_0$ coins of the second highest denomination. Thus, the minimum value of the loot they must leave behind is:

